HEADWORD: Penstemon
<hw>Penstemon</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A large genus of subshrubs
or herbs having showy blue or purple or red or yellow or white flowers;
found mostly in Western North America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Penstemon</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
